INSERT INTO `post` VALUES (1,1,1,'Top 10 Mobile Development Trends You Should Follow','<p>Year 2017 emerged as a benchmark year for the trends shaping mobile development and there are several reasons responsible for this. Two of the major reasons are - infiltration of newer and more exciting technologies into this sector and the cost of adopting mobile apps for smaller businesses expected to be well within the reach in 2018.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 13.6406px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: 19px; font-family: \'Myriad W01 Regular\'; color: #454546; letter-spacing: 0.03em;\">Following are the top 10 trends that are expected to shape mobile development in 2018 and beyond -</p>\r\n<ol class=\"h3 img-list\" style=\"margin: 6.8125px 0px 13.6406px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal; font-family: \'Myriad W01 Regular\'; color: #454546; float: left; clear: both;\">\r\n<li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 4px 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 18px; line-height: normal; color: #226477; list-style-position: inside; clear: both;\">\r\n<h3 style=\"margin: 6.8125px 0px 10px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 18px; line-height: normal; letter-spacing: 0px; display: inline-block;\">Artificial Intelligence is Now Real</h3>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 13.6406px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: 19px; color: #454546; letter-spacing: 0.03em;\"><img class=\"art-inner-img\" style=\"margin: 0px 10px 15px 0px; padding: 5px; border: 1px solid #d9d9d9; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; float: left;\" title=\"Artificial Intelligence is Now Real\" src=\"https://cdn.flatworldsolutions.com/IT-services/images/icons/ai.jpg\" alt=\"Artificial Intelligence is Now Real\" />According to Gartner, year 2018 has witnessed over 300% increase in the investments made on Artificial Intelligence (AI) for mobile such as mobile chatbots, which make great substitutes for functions carried out by numerous websites and apps. Features like these make it simple to perform a variety of tasks on mobile devices forgoing the need for downloading several apps. Therefore, AI in mobile app development is expected to govern mobile developments in 2018.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 4px 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 18px; line-height: normal; color: #226477; list-style-position: inside; clear: both;\">\r\n<h3 style=\"margin: 6.8125px 0px 10px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 18px; line-height: normal; letter-spacing: 0px; display: inline-block;\">App Streaming is Expected Go Mainstream</h3>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 13.6406px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: 19px; color: #454546; letter-spacing: 0.03em;\"><img class=\"art-inner-img\" style=\"margin: 0px 10px 15px 0px; padding: 5px; border: 1px solid #d9d9d9; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; float: left;\" title=\"App Streaming is Expected Go Mainstream\" src=\"https://cdn.flatworldsolutions.com/IT-services/images/icons/app-stream.jpg\" alt=\"App Streaming is Expected Go Mainstream\" />Lack of space on phone memory is one of the major reasons causing app abandonment by the users. App streaming technology was designed to address this concern of mobile app users. Just like video streaming, app streaming also enables the users to harness some features of an app directly from the app store, without downloading it. Therefore, App Streaming opens vast possibilities, for example, app developers can give a taste of their app\'s experience to the users without any installation hassles. This will potentially improve user retention as the user acquisition costs will also be hugely reduced.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 4px 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 18px; line-height: normal; color: #226477; list-style-position: inside; clear: both;\">\r\n<h3 style=\"margin: 6.8125px 0px 10px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 18px; line-height: normal; letter-spacing: 0px; display: inline-block;\">Utility and Augmented Reality Apps to be Integrated</h3>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 13.6406px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: 19px; color: #454546; letter-spacing: 0.03em;\"><img class=\"art-inner-img\" style=\"margin: 0px 10px 15px 0px; padding: 5px; border: 1px solid #d9d9d9; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; float: left;\" title=\"Utility and Augmented Reality Apps to be Integrated\" src=\"https://cdn.flatworldsolutions.com/IT-services/images/icons/aug-reality.jpg\" alt=\"Utility and Augmented Reality Apps to be Integrated\" />Although&nbsp;<a style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; color: #2aaadc; outline: 0px; text-decoration-line: none;\" href=\"https://www.flatworldsolutions.com/IT-services/mobile-applications/augmented-reality-app-development.php\">Augmented Reality apps</a>&nbsp;are often considered to be gimmicky, they are expected to make one of the most actively engaging apps when integrated with utility apps. The best part is one of its major business benefits is to boost the engagement of millennial customers. Therefore, this integration is one of the major mobile development trends, which can be expected in 2018 and beyond.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 4px 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 18px; line-height: normal; color: #226477; list-style-position: inside; clear: both;\">\r\n<h3 style=\"margin: 6.8125px 0px 10px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 18px; line-height: normal; letter-spacing: 0px; display: inline-block;\">Mobile Security Will Be the Top Priority</h3>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 13.6406px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: 19px; color: #454546; letter-spacing: 0.03em;\"><img class=\"art-inner-img\" style=\"margin: 0px 10px 15px 0px; padding: 5px; border: 1px solid #d9d9d9; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; float: left;\" title=\"Mobile Security Will Be the Top Priority\" src=\"https://cdn.flatworldsolutions.com/IT-services/images/icons/mobile-security.jpg\" alt=\"Mobile Security Will Be the Top Priority\" />With mobile phones evolving into wallets and purses, security is undoubtedly a major concern. \"Hewlett Packard Enterprise Mobile Application Security Report 2016\" states that 96.52% of mobile apps examined failed to clear one or more security tests. Today, most of the mobile apps mainly focus on UX and UI and completely skip security. Apps that seek access to unrelated data, such as a fitness app that asks the access to a user\'s calendar data, often rely on advertising and analytics framework and create unnecessary log files. All these make it easy for malicious attackers to quickly access and steal sensitive and private data of the app users. Therefore, app developers are expected to follow certain best practices, which include -</p>\r\n<ul style=\"margin: 1px 0px 1px 10px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal; color: #454546; list-style: disc;\">\r\n<li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: 21px; text-align: left; list-style-position: outside; background: none !important;\">Constantly analyzing the apps during and after the usage to detect any data leakage</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: 21px; text-align: left; list-style-position: outside; background: none !important;\">Stop storing sensitive and private data in external storage without encrypting it</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: 21px; text-align: left; list-style-position: outside; background: none !important;\">Ensuring that all the applications are accurately transmitting data over SSL</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 4px 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 18px; line-height: normal; color: #226477; list-style-position: inside; clear: both;\">\r\n<h3 style=\"margin: 6.8125px 0px 10px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 18px; line-height: normal; letter-spacing: 0px; display: inline-block;\">Rise of Cloud-driven Mobile Apps</h3>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 13.6406px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: 19px; color: #454546; letter-spacing: 0.03em;\"><img class=\"art-inner-img\" style=\"margin: 0px 10px 15px 0px; padding: 5px; border: 1px solid #d9d9d9; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; float: left;\" title=\"Rise of Cloud-driven Mobile Apps\" src=\"https://cdn.flatworldsolutions.com/IT-services/images/icons/cloud-mobile-apps.jpg\" alt=\"Rise of Cloud-driven Mobile Apps\" />From tech professionals to customers, everybody is aware of the Cloud technology and its impact on our collective lives. Today, cloud computing is successfully integrated with the mobile apps. Now, users can expect functional mobile apps that directly access data from the Cloud, taking minimum space in the internal memory of smartphones. According to a research carried out by Cisco, 90% of the mobile data traffic will be driven by cloud apps, by 2019.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 4px 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 18px; line-height: normal; color: #226477; list-style-position: inside; clear: both;\">\r\n<h3 style=\"margin: 6.8125px 0px 10px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 18px; line-height: normal; letter-spacing: 0px; display: inline-block;\">Boom of Location-based Services</h3>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 13.6406px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: 19px; color: #454546; letter-spacing: 0.03em;\"><img class=\"art-inner-img\" style=\"margin: 0px 10px 15px 0px; padding: 5px; border: 1px solid #d9d9d9; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; float: left;\" title=\"Location Based Services\" src=\"https://cdn.flatworldsolutions.com/IT-services/images/icons/location-based-services.jpg\" alt=\"Location Based Services\" />With consumers using mobile devices to update their social network about where they shop, visit, or eat, with the help of location based mobile networks, this technology is expected to boon in the year 2018 and beyond. This technology enables users to seamlessly interact with their business associates and friends, while they are traveling.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 4px 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 18px; line-height: normal; color: #226477; list-style-position: inside; clear: both;\">\r\n<h3 style=\"margin: 6.8125px 0px 10px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 18px; line-height: normal; letter-spacing: 0px; display: inline-block;\">Micro-apps and Enterprise Apps to Flourish</h3>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 13.6406px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: 19px; color: #454546; letter-spacing: 0.03em;\"><img class=\"art-inner-img\" style=\"margin: 0px 10px 15px 0px; padding: 5px; border: 1px solid #d9d9d9; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; float: left;\" title=\"Micro-apps and Enterprise Apps to Flourish\" src=\"https://cdn.flatworldsolutions.com/IT-services/images/icons/micro-enterprise-apps.jpg\" alt=\"Micro-apps and Enterprise Apps to Flourish\" />While micro-apps aim to carry out targeted business operations to take lesser loads, enterprise apps are designed to streamline, manage, and restructure important business operations on the go. Both these apps have made phenomenal difference to businesses and are expected to impact mobile development 2018 and beyond.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 4px 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 18px; line-height: normal; color: #226477; list-style-position: inside; clear: both;\">\r\n<h3 style=\"margin: 6.8125px 0px 10px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 18px; line-height: normal; letter-spacing: 0px; display: inline-block;\">Wearable Devices to Get Attention</h3>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 13.6406px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: 19px; color: #454546; letter-spacing: 0.03em;\"><img class=\"art-inner-img\" style=\"margin: 0px 10px 15px 0px; padding: 5px; border: 1px solid #d9d9d9; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; float: left;\" title=\"Wearable Devices to Get Attention\" src=\"https://cdn.flatworldsolutions.com/IT-services/images/icons/wearable-devices.jpg\" alt=\"Wearable Devices to Get Attention\" />As per the International Data Corporation (IDC), wearable devices market is predicted to grow at a rate of 20.3% per annum. This being one of the latest mobile development trends, it is expected to result in 213.6 million units to be shipped by the year 2020. Some of the amazing wearable devices witnessed in 2018 include Fitbit Flex 2, Pebble 2, Google Daydream View, Apple Watch Series 1, etc.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 4px 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 18px; line-height: normal; color: #226477; list-style-position: inside; clear: both;\">\r\n<h3 style=\"margin: 6.8125px 0px 10px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 18px; line-height: normal; letter-spacing: 0px; display: inline-block;\">m-commerce Will Set New Standards</h3>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 13.6406px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: 19px; color: #454546; letter-spacing: 0.03em;\"><img class=\"art-inner-img\" style=\"margin: 0px 10px 15px 0px; padding: 5px; border: 1px solid #d9d9d9; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; float: left;\" title=\"m-commerce Will Set New Standards\" src=\"https://cdn.flatworldsolutions.com/IT-services/images/icons/m-commerce.jpg\" alt=\"m-commerce Will Set New Standards\" />With a considerable number of users preferring to complete their purchases using Apple Pay and Google Wallet, m-commerce will emerge as one of the important trends in mobile development. m-commerce payment facility coupled with wearable devices is expected to take a new shape in the year 2018.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 4px 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 18px; line-height: normal; color: #226477; list-style-position: inside; clear: both;\">\r\n<h3 style=\"margin: 6.8125px 0px 10px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 18px; line-height: normal; letter-spacing: 0px; display: inline-block;\">AMP Project Transforms Mobile Landscape</h3>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 13.6406px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: 19px; color: #454546; letter-spacing: 0.03em;\"><img class=\"art-inner-img\" style=\"margin: 0px 10px 15px 0px; padding: 5px; border: 1px solid #d9d9d9; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; line-height: normal; float: left;\" title=\"AMP Project Transforms Mobile Landscape\" src=\"https://cdn.flatworldsolutions.com/IT-services/images/icons/amp.jpg\" alt=\"AMP Project Transforms Mobile Landscape\" />Accelerated Mobile pages (AMP), is designed to improve the loading speed of mobile apps on mobile. Another technology called progressive web apps, a technology which makes mobile websites look and feel like mobile apps, is also being constantly used and serves as an alternative to developing and updating the native apps. These are the trends shaping mobile development in 2018 and beyond.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h2 style=\"margin: 6.8125px 0px 3px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 21px; line-height: normal; font-family: \'Myriad W01 Regular\'; color: #226477;\">Summing Up</h2>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 13.6406px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: 19px; font-family: \'Myriad W01 Regular\'; color: #454546; letter-spacing: 0.03em;\">Although these are the top trends expected to shape mobile development in 2018 and beyond, numerous other technologies, such as Altered Reality, serverless apps, IoT apps, etc. are also expected to make an impact. While an increasing number of people are investing in developing and buying apps, users will continue to experience hassles with poorly built apps. Therefore, year 2018 demands developers to focus on delivering standout mobile apps that add value to the users\' day-to-day life.</p>','2018-12-14 00:25:49','2018-12-14 00:25:49'),(2,6,1,'Top 7 IOT Predictions to look forward to in 2020','<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 13.6406px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: 19px; font-family: \'Myriad W01 Regular\'; color: #454546; letter-spacing: 0.03em;\">Internet is engulfing all technologies at a brisk speed, resulting in the creation of a world where every other thing relates to the internet. The internet is no more limited to just computers, smartphones, and tablets. It has now touched hearts of several other devices and is making our lives more convenient by enabling us to communicate with devices with ease and simplicity.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 13.6406px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: 19px; font-family: \'Myriad W01 Regular\'; color: #454546; letter-spacing: 0.03em;\">The phenomena \'Internet of Things\' is an umbrella term used to describe devices that relate to internet. Today, Internet of Things has become a mainstream topic and the technology world is striving hard to make key inroads towards development of IoT.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 13.6406px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: 19px; font-family: \'Myriad W01 Regular\'; color: #454546; letter-spacing: 0.03em;\">It is expected that spending on IoT will reach $772 Billion by 2018 resulting in stratospheric development of IoT. But what does the future hold for Internet of Things?</p>\r\n<h2 class=\"clear\" style=\"margin: 6.8125px 0px 3px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 21px; line-height: normal; font-family: \'Myriad W01 Regular\'; color: #226477; clear: both;\">IoT in 2020 - Top 7 Predictions</h2>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 13.6406px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: 19px; font-family: \'Myriad W01 Regular\'; color: #454546; letter-spacing: 0.03em;\">This is an exciting phase for IoT. The world is awakening to the potential of IoT and is embracing it at a tremendous speed. Tech giants are investing massive capital in developing IoT while some of the best minds across the world are focused on pushing the limits of this eco-system.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 13.6406px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: 19px; font-family: \'Myriad W01 Regular\'; color: #454546; letter-spacing: 0.03em;\">The upshot? IoT is developing immensely and we are all geared up to witness some breathtaking changes in the upcoming years.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 13.6406px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: 19px; font-family: \'Myriad W01 Regular\'; color: #454546; letter-spacing: 0.03em;\">Want to know top IoT predictions for 2020? Here we make seven for Internet of Things predictions which reflect a lot about the future of IoT and how it will look by 2020.</p>\r\n<ol class=\"image-text h3\" style=\"margin: 6.8125px 0px 13.6406px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal; font-family: \'Myriad W01 Regular\'; color: #454546; float: left !important;\">\r\n<li style=\"margin: 1px 0px 1px 20px; padding: 4px 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 18px; line-height: normal; color: #226477; list-style-position: outside; clear: both;\">\r\n<h3 style=\"margin: 6.625px 0px 3px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 18px; line-height: normal; letter-spacing: 0px;\">By 2020, Internet of Things Will Connect 21 Billion Devices</h3>\r\n<img class=\"art-inner-img border\" style=\"margin: 0px 15px 10px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 1px solid #d9d9d9; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal; color: #454546; float: left;\" src=\"https://cdn.flatworldsolutions.com/IT-services/images/thumbs/iot-will-connect-billion-devices.jpg\" alt=\"IoT will connect 21 Billion Devices by 2020\" />\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 13.25px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: 19px; color: #454546; letter-spacing: 0.03em;\">The Internet of Things has taken the technology world by storm. And its limitless applications have fueled its popularity. Hence, every year more and more devices are getting connected with IoT.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 13.25px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: 19px; color: #454546; letter-spacing: 0.03em;\">In 2015, there were 4.9 million devices related to IoT, but by the end of 2016 this number skyrocketed to 3.9 billion. Within one year, the number increased from million to billion and experts believe that this sensational rate of growth will continue in the upcoming years as well.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 13.25px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: 19px; color: #454546; letter-spacing: 0.03em;\">It is estimated that by 2020, there will be up to 21 billion devices across the globe connected with \'Internet of Things\'. This number is enough to reflect how enormous the ecosystem of IoT would become and how it will be practically impossible for a person to stay away from this phenomenon.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin: 1px 0px 1px 20px; padding: 4px 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 18px; line-height: normal; color: #226477; list-style-position: outside; clear: both;\">\r\n<h3 style=\"margin: 6.625px 0px 3px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 18px; line-height: normal; letter-spacing: 0px;\">Cities Will Continue to Become Smart</h3>\r\n<img class=\"art-inner-img border\" style=\"margin: 0px 15px 10px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 1px solid #d9d9d9; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal; color: #454546; float: left;\" src=\"https://cdn.flatworldsolutions.com/IT-services/images/thumbs/cities-will-continue-to-become-smart.jpg\" alt=\"Cities will Continue to Become Smart\" />\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 13.25px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: 19px; color: #454546; letter-spacing: 0.03em;\">Internet of Things won\'t only be limited to devices and things, it will have wider applications. One such obvious application of Internet of Things is the functioning of cities.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 13.25px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: 19px; color: #454546; letter-spacing: 0.03em;\">In future, cities will become smart courtesy the data gained from IoT and will enable its citizen to enjoy a hassle free and comfortable life. Thanks to IoT, cities will become more efficient &amp; will be able to save money, time &amp; other resources.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 13.25px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: 19px; color: #454546; letter-spacing: 0.03em;\">Data will be collected, managed and automated through video camera surveillance systems, taxi services and visitor kiosks.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 13.25px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: 19px; color: #454546; letter-spacing: 0.03em;\">Modern cities make it easier for citizens to travel from one place to another and access basic amenities. This system will also enable cities to maintain a detailed profile of its citizens and curb crime and other issues.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin: 1px 0px 1px 20px; padding: 4px 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 18px; line-height: normal; color: #226477; list-style-position: outside; clear: both;\">\r\n<h3 style=\"margin: 6.625px 0px 3px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 18px; line-height: normal; letter-spacing: 0px;\">IoT Will See Fragmentation</h3>\r\n<img class=\"art-inner-img border\" style=\"margin: 0px 15px 10px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 1px solid #d9d9d9; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal; color: #454546; float: left;\" src=\"https://cdn.flatworldsolutions.com/IT-services/images/thumbs/iot-will-see-fragmentation.jpg\" alt=\"IoT will see Fragmentation\" />\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 13.25px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: 19px; color: #454546; letter-spacing: 0.03em;\">The growth and development of IoT will not only be vertical, in fact, it will see a lot of fragmentation. This obvious fragmentation will cause serious issues of compatibility as companies will struggle to create and maintain device standards and certifications.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 13.25px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: 19px; color: #454546; letter-spacing: 0.03em;\">This will push companies to come together and create an eco-system that channelizes smooth running of IoT. It will open new avenues for tech personals to create systems that collaborate with other devices and have universal adaptability.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 13.25px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: 19px; color: #454546; letter-spacing: 0.03em;\">This fragmentation could also mean that we would see several eco-systems of devices being developed and facilitated under one bigger IoT ecosystem.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin: 1px 0px 1px 20px; padding: 4px 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 18px; line-height: normal; color: #226477; list-style-position: outside; clear: both;\">\r\n<h3 style=\"margin: 6.625px 0px 3px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 18px; line-height: normal; letter-spacing: 0px;\">There Will Be Increase in Security Concerns</h3>\r\n<img class=\"art-inner-img border\" style=\"margin: 0px 15px 10px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 1px solid #d9d9d9; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal; color: #454546; float: left;\" src=\"https://cdn.flatworldsolutions.com/IT-services/images/thumbs/there-will-be-increase-in-security-concerns.jpg\" alt=\"There will be Increase in Security Concerns\" />\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 13.25px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: 19px; color: #454546; letter-spacing: 0.03em;\">Security is already a widely discussed facet of Internet of Things and it is believed that as IoT grows, the security concerns will grow as well.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 13.25px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: 19px; color: #454546; letter-spacing: 0.03em;\">Internet of Things offers limitless opportunities to enhance communication between devices and data sharing, but this same feature makes it highly vulnerable from the point of view of security.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 13.25px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: 19px; color: #454546; letter-spacing: 0.03em;\">As the network of connected devices grows, it becomes daunting to regulate it and to keep the data safe. Companies will have to develop better solutions to ensure that data remains safe and there are no potential leakages in the network.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin: 1px 0px 1px 20px; padding: 4px 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 18px; line-height: normal; color: #226477; list-style-position: outside; clear: both;\">\r\n<h3 style=\"margin: 6.625px 0px 3px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 18px; line-height: normal; letter-spacing: 0px;\">A Boost to Artificial Intelligence</h3>\r\n<img class=\"art-inner-img border\" style=\"margin: 0px 15px 10px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 1px solid #d9d9d9; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal; color: #454546; float: left;\" src=\"https://cdn.flatworldsolutions.com/IT-services/images/thumbs/boost-to-artificial-intelligence.jpg\" alt=\"A Boost to Artificial Intelligence\" />\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 13.25px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: 19px; color: #454546; letter-spacing: 0.03em;\">Internet of Things will enable devices to collect data about you. From thermostats to vehicles and to even coffee makers, all devices will collect information about your behavior. This data will get stored in the cloud and will be used to make the device \'learn\' without any manual programming. This learning known as machine learning is a critical aspect of artificial intelligence and the growth of IoT will boost artificial intelligence as well.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin: 1px 0px 1px 20px; padding: 4px 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 18px; line-height: normal; color: #226477; list-style-position: outside; clear: both;\">\r\n<h3 style=\"margin: 6.625px 0px 3px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 18px; line-height: normal; letter-spacing: 0px;\">Companies Will Have to Develop Data Processing Solutions</h3>\r\n<img class=\"art-inner-img border\" style=\"margin: 0px 15px 10px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 1px solid #d9d9d9; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal; color: #454546; float: left;\" src=\"https://cdn.flatworldsolutions.com/IT-services/images/thumbs/companies-develop-data-processing-solutions.jpg\" alt=\"Companies Will Have to Develop Data Processing Solutions\" />\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 13.25px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: 19px; color: #454546; letter-spacing: 0.03em;\">The growth of IoT will result in accumulation of enormous data which will need to be processed and analyzed. The current data processing systems won\'t be enough and hence companies will have to invest in solutions that are faster and cheaper.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li style=\"margin: 1px 0px 1px 20px; padding: 4px 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 18px; line-height: normal; color: #226477; list-style-position: outside; clear: both;\">\r\n<h3 style=\"margin: 6.625px 0px 3px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-weight: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 18px; line-height: normal; letter-spacing: 0px;\">There Will Be Big Money</h3>\r\n<img class=\"art-inner-img border\" style=\"margin: 0px 15px 10px 0px; padding: 0px; border: 1px solid #d9d9d9; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: normal; color: #454546; float: left;\" src=\"https://cdn.flatworldsolutions.com/IT-services/images/thumbs/there-will-be-big-money.jpg\" alt=\"There will be Big Money\" />\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 13.25px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 15px; line-height: 19px; color: #454546; letter-spacing: 0.03em;\">The technology world has acknowledged Internet of Things\' ability to enhance customer experience. Hence there will be no dearth in funding and capital for IoT. It is predicted that by 2021, IoT spending will reach $6 trillion.</p>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>','2018-12-14 00:29:53','2018-12-14 00:31:26'),(3,7,1,'What exactly can you do with Python?','<p id=\"2db8\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--figure\" style=\"margin: 38px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">If you&rsquo;re thinking of learning Python &mdash; or if you recently started learning it &mdash; you may be asking yourself:</p>\r\n<blockquote id=\"2da2\" class=\"graf graf--pullquote graf--startsWithDoubleQuote graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 55px 0px 0px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.68); border: none; padding: 0px 0px 0px 50px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.22; font-family: medium-content-slab-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-style: italic; font-size: 30px; line-height: 1.48; letter-spacing: -0.012em; text-indent: -0.32em;\"><span class=\"markup--strong markup--pullquote-strong\" style=\"--baseline-multiplier: 0.22;\">&ldquo;What exactly can I use Python&nbsp;for?&rdquo;</span></blockquote>\r\n<p id=\"536f\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--pullquote\" style=\"margin: 54px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">Well that&rsquo;s a tricky question to answer, because there are so many applications for Python.</p>\r\n<p id=\"2c50\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">But over time, I have observed that there are 3 main popular applications for Python:</p>\r\n<ul class=\"postList\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none none; counter-reset: post 0; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84); font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, \'Open Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', sans-serif; font-size: 20px;\">\r\n<li id=\"505e\" class=\"graf graf--li graf-after--p\" style=\"margin-left: 30px; margin-bottom: 14px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em;\">Web Development</li>\r\n<li id=\"be98\" class=\"graf graf--li graf-after--li\" style=\"margin-left: 30px; margin-bottom: 14px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em;\">Data Science &mdash; including machine learning, data analysis, and data visualization</li>\r\n<li id=\"65f6\" class=\"graf graf--li graf-after--li\" style=\"margin-left: 30px; margin-bottom: 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em;\">Scripting</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p id=\"ef77\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--li\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">Let&rsquo;s talk about each of them in turn.</p>\r\n<h3 id=\"c75e\" class=\"graf graf--h3 graf-after--p\" style=\"font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, \'Lucida Grande\', \'Lucida Sans Unicode\', \'Lucida Sans\', Geneva, Arial, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -0.015em; margin: 56px 0px 0px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84); --baseline-multiplier: 0.22; font-size: 34px; line-height: 1.15;\"><span class=\"markup--strong markup--h3-strong\">Web Development</span></h3>\r\n<p id=\"0790\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--h3\" style=\"margin: 8px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">Web frameworks that are based on Python like&nbsp;<span class=\"markup--strong markup--p-strong\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Django</span>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<span class=\"markup--strong markup--p-strong\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Flask</span>&nbsp;have recently become very popular for web development.</p>\r\n<p id=\"bd8b\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">These web frameworks help you create server-side code (backend code) in Python. That&rsquo;s the code that runs on your server, as opposed to on users&rsquo; devices and browsers (front-end code). If you&rsquo;re not familiar with the difference between backend code and front-end code, please see my footnote below.</p>\r\n<h4 id=\"d0ec\" class=\"graf graf--h4 graf-after--p\" style=\"font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, \'Lucida Grande\', \'Lucida Sans Unicode\', \'Lucida Sans\', Geneva, Arial, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -0.012em; margin: 30px 0px 0px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84); --baseline-multiplier: 0.22; font-size: 26px; line-height: 1.22;\"><span class=\"markup--strong markup--h4-strong\" style=\"font-weight: inherit;\">But wait, why do I need a web framework?</span></h4>\r\n<p id=\"0f1c\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--h4\" style=\"margin: 6px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">That&rsquo;s because a web framework makes it easier to build common backend logic. This includes mapping different URLs to chunks of Python code, dealing with databases, and generating HTML files users see on their browsers.</p>\r\n<h4 id=\"3b6e\" class=\"graf graf--h4 graf-after--p\" style=\"font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, \'Lucida Grande\', \'Lucida Sans Unicode\', \'Lucida Sans\', Geneva, Arial, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -0.012em; margin: 30px 0px 0px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84); --baseline-multiplier: 0.22; font-size: 26px; line-height: 1.22;\"><span class=\"markup--strong markup--h4-strong\" style=\"font-weight: inherit;\">Which Python web framework should I&nbsp;use?</span></h4>\r\n<p id=\"aedd\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--h4\" style=\"margin: 6px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">Django and Flask are two of the most popular Python web frameworks. I&rsquo;d recommend using one of them if you&rsquo;re just getting started.</p>\r\n<h4 id=\"1875\" class=\"graf graf--h4 graf-after--p\" style=\"font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, \'Lucida Grande\', \'Lucida Sans Unicode\', \'Lucida Sans\', Geneva, Arial, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -0.012em; margin: 30px 0px 0px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84); --baseline-multiplier: 0.22; font-size: 26px; line-height: 1.22;\"><span class=\"markup--strong markup--h4-strong\" style=\"font-weight: inherit;\">What&rsquo;s the difference between Django and&nbsp;Flask?</span></h4>\r\n<p id=\"bf5d\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--h4\" style=\"margin: 6px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">There&rsquo;s an&nbsp;<a class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" style=\"background-color: transparent; text-decoration-line: none; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54); background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: linear-gradient(to right, currentcolor 100%, currentcolor 0px); background-size: 1px 1px; background-position: 0px calc(1em + 1px);\" href=\"https://www.codementor.io/garethdwyer/flask-vs-django-why-flask-might-be-better-4xs7mdf8v\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-href=\"https://www.codementor.io/garethdwyer/flask-vs-django-why-flask-might-be-better-4xs7mdf8v\">excellent article</a>&nbsp;about this topic by Gareth Dwyer, so let me quote it here:</p>\r\n<p id=\"ff65\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\"><span class=\"markup--strong markup--p-strong\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><em class=\"markup--em markup--p-em\" style=\"font-feature-settings: \'liga\', \'salt\';\">&lt;begin quote&gt;</em></span></p>\r\n<p id=\"9ddf\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">Main contrasts:</p>\r\n<ul class=\"postList\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none none; counter-reset: post 0; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84); font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, \'Open Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', sans-serif; font-size: 20px;\">\r\n<li id=\"7244\" class=\"graf graf--li graf-after--p\" style=\"margin-left: 30px; margin-bottom: 14px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em;\">Flask provides simplicity, flexibility and fine-grained control. It is unopinionated (it lets you decide how you want to implement things).</li>\r\n<li id=\"dc55\" class=\"graf graf--li graf-after--li\" style=\"margin-left: 30px; margin-bottom: 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em;\">Django provides an all-inclusive experience: you get an admin panel, database interfaces, an&nbsp;<a class=\"markup--anchor markup--li-anchor\" style=\"background-color: transparent; text-decoration-line: none; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54); background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: linear-gradient(to right, currentcolor 100%, currentcolor 0px); background-size: 1px 1px; background-position: 0px calc(1em + 1px);\" href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/1279613/what-is-an-orm-and-where-can-i-learn-more-about-it\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/1279613/what-is-an-orm-and-where-can-i-learn-more-about-it\">ORM [object-relational mapping]</a>, and directory structure for your apps and projects out of the box.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p id=\"37a5\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--li\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">You should probably choose:</p>\r\n<ul class=\"postList\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none none; counter-reset: post 0; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84); font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, \'Open Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', sans-serif; font-size: 20px;\">\r\n<li id=\"a6bf\" class=\"graf graf--li graf-after--p\" style=\"margin-left: 30px; margin-bottom: 14px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em;\">Flask, if you&rsquo;re focused on the experience and learning opportunities, or if you want more control about which components to use (such as what databases you want to use and how you want to interact with them).</li>\r\n<li id=\"84e1\" class=\"graf graf--li graf-after--li\" style=\"margin-left: 30px; margin-bottom: 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em;\">Django, if you&rsquo;re focused on the final product. Especially if you&rsquo;re working on a straight-forward application such as a news site, an e-store, or blog, and you want there to always be a single, obvious way of doing things.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p id=\"08d8\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--li\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\"><span class=\"markup--strong markup--p-strong\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\"><em class=\"markup--em markup--p-em\" style=\"font-feature-settings: \'liga\', \'salt\';\">&lt;/end quote&gt;</em></span></p>\r\n<p id=\"8a5e\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">In other words, If you&rsquo;re a beginner, Flask is probably a better choice because it has fewer components to deal with. Also, Flask is a better choice if you want more customization.</p>\r\n<p id=\"c101\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">On the other hand, if you&rsquo;re looking to build something straight-forward, Django will probably let you get there faster.</p>\r\n<p id=\"a8a9\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">Now, if you&rsquo;re looking to learn Django, I recommend the book called Django for Beginners. You can find it&nbsp;<a class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" style=\"background-color: transparent; text-decoration-line: none; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54); background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: linear-gradient(to right, currentcolor 100%, currentcolor 0px); background-size: 1px 1px; background-position: 0px calc(1em + 1px);\" href=\"http://csdojo.io/dj\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-href=\"http://csdojo.io/dj\">here</a>.</p>\r\n<p id=\"b413\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">You can also find the free sample chapters of that book&nbsp;<a class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" style=\"background-color: transparent; text-decoration-line: none; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54); background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: linear-gradient(to right, currentcolor 100%, currentcolor 0px); background-size: 1px 1px; background-position: 0px calc(1em + 1px);\" href=\"https://djangoforbeginners.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-href=\"https://djangoforbeginners.com/\">here</a>.</p>\r\n<p id=\"43bd\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">Okay, let&rsquo;s go to the next topic!</p>\r\n<h3 id=\"1e5a\" class=\"graf graf--h3 graf-after--p\" style=\"font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, \'Lucida Grande\', \'Lucida Sans Unicode\', \'Lucida Sans\', Geneva, Arial, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -0.015em; margin: 56px 0px 0px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84); --baseline-multiplier: 0.22; font-size: 34px; line-height: 1.15;\"><span class=\"markup--strong markup--h3-strong\">Data Science &mdash; including machine learning, data analysis, and data visualization</span></h3>\r\n<h4 id=\"e91f\" class=\"graf graf--h4 graf-after--h3\" style=\"font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, \'Lucida Grande\', \'Lucida Sans Unicode\', \'Lucida Sans\', Geneva, Arial, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -0.012em; margin: 31px 0px 0px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84); --baseline-multiplier: 0.22; font-size: 26px; line-height: 1.22;\"><span class=\"markup--strong markup--h4-strong\" style=\"font-weight: inherit;\">First of all, let&rsquo;s review what machine learning&nbsp;<span class=\"markup--em markup--h4-em\" style=\"font-feature-settings: \'liga\', \'salt\';\">is</span>.</span></h4>\r\n<p id=\"6e8b\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--h4\" style=\"margin: 6px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">I think the best way to explain what machine learning is would be to give you a simple example.</p>\r\n<p id=\"966c\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">Let&rsquo;s say you want to develop a program that automatically detects what&rsquo;s in a picture.</p>\r\n<p id=\"c2be\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">So, given this picture below (Picture 1), you want your program to recognize that it&rsquo;s a dog.</p>\r\n<figure id=\"6323\" class=\"graf graf--figure graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 43px 0px 0px; position: relative; clear: both; outline: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; user-select: auto; z-index: 100; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84); font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, \'Open Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', sans-serif; font-size: 20px;\">\r\n<div class=\"aspectRatioPlaceholder is-locked\" style=\"position: relative; width: 700px; margin: 0px auto; max-width: 700px; max-height: 443px;\">\r\n<div class=\"aspectRatioPlaceholder-fill\" style=\"padding-bottom: 443.094px;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"progressiveMedia js-progressiveMedia graf-image is-canvasLoaded is-imageLoaded\" style=\"position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 700px; height: 443px; margin: auto; box-sizing: border-box; background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); transition: background 0.2s ease 0s; cursor: zoom-in; max-width: 100%;\" data-image-id=\"0*Mbj3L2cl0zzT2A0L\" data-width=\"4774\" data-height=\"3024\" data-action=\"zoom\" data-action-value=\"0*Mbj3L2cl0zzT2A0L\" data-scroll=\"native\"><canvas class=\"progressiveMedia-canvas js-progressiveMedia-canvas\" style=\"display: block; vertical-align: baseline; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 700px; height: 443px; margin: auto; box-sizing: border-box; visibility: hidden; opacity: 0; backface-visibility: hidden; transition: visibility 0s linear 0.5s, opacity 0.1s ease 0.4s;\" width=\"75\" height=\"47\"></canvas><img class=\"progressiveMedia-image js-progressiveMedia-image\" style=\"border: 0px; display: block; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 700px; height: 443px; margin: auto; box-sizing: border-box; z-index: 100; visibility: visible; opacity: 1; backface-visibility: hidden; transition: visibility 0s linear 0s, opacity 0.4s ease 0s;\" src=\"https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/1600/0*Mbj3L2cl0zzT2A0L\" alt=\"\" data-src=\"https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/1600/0*Mbj3L2cl0zzT2A0L\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<figcaption class=\"imageCaption\" style=\"position: relative; left: 0px; width: 700px; top: 0px; margin-top: 10px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.68); outline: 0px; text-align: center; z-index: 300; --baseline-multiplier: 0.22; font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, \'Lucida Grande\', \'Lucida Sans Unicode\', \'Lucida Sans\', Geneva, Arial, sans-serif; font-feature-settings: \'liga\', \'lnum\'; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4; letter-spacing: 0px;\">Picture 1</figcaption></figure>\r\n<p id=\"3da0\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--figure\" style=\"margin: 38px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">Given this other one below (Picture 2), you want your program to recognize that it&rsquo;s a table.</p>\r\n<figure id=\"531b\" class=\"graf graf--figure graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 43px 0px 0px; position: relative; clear: both; outline: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; user-select: auto; z-index: 100; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84); font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, \'Open Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', sans-serif; font-size: 20px;\">\r\n<div class=\"aspectRatioPlaceholder is-locked\" style=\"position: relative; width: 700px; margin: 0px auto; max-width: 700px; max-height: 467px;\">\r\n<div class=\"aspectRatioPlaceholder-fill\" style=\"padding-bottom: 466.891px;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"progressiveMedia js-progressiveMedia graf-image is-canvasLoaded is-imageLoaded\" style=\"position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 700px; height: 466.891px; margin: auto; box-sizing: border-box; background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); transition: background 0.2s ease 0s; cursor: zoom-in; max-width: 100%;\" data-image-id=\"0*gxTn_CbMyCcQ1NFV\" data-width=\"6000\" data-height=\"4004\" data-action=\"zoom\" data-action-value=\"0*gxTn_CbMyCcQ1NFV\" data-scroll=\"native\"><canvas class=\"progressiveMedia-canvas js-progressiveMedia-canvas\" style=\"display: block; vertical-align: baseline; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 700px; height: 466.891px; margin: auto; box-sizing: border-box; visibility: hidden; opacity: 0; backface-visibility: hidden; transition: visibility 0s linear 0.5s, opacity 0.1s ease 0.4s;\" width=\"75\" height=\"50\"></canvas><img class=\"progressiveMedia-image js-progressiveMedia-image\" style=\"border: 0px; display: block; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 700px; height: 466.891px; margin: auto; box-sizing: border-box; z-index: 100; visibility: visible; opacity: 1; backface-visibility: hidden; transition: visibility 0s linear 0s, opacity 0.4s ease 0s;\" src=\"https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/1600/0*gxTn_CbMyCcQ1NFV\" alt=\"\" data-src=\"https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/1600/0*gxTn_CbMyCcQ1NFV\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<figcaption class=\"imageCaption\" style=\"position: relative; left: 0px; width: 700px; top: 0px; margin-top: 10px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.68); outline: 0px; text-align: center; z-index: 300; --baseline-multiplier: 0.22; font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, \'Lucida Grande\', \'Lucida Sans Unicode\', \'Lucida Sans\', Geneva, Arial, sans-serif; font-feature-settings: \'liga\', \'lnum\'; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4; letter-spacing: 0px;\">Picture 2</figcaption></figure>\r\n<p id=\"b78f\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--figure\" style=\"margin: 38px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">You might say, well, I can just write some code to do that. For example, maybe if there are a lot of light brown pixels in the picture, then we can say that it&rsquo;s a dog.</p>\r\n<p id=\"86b9\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">Or maybe, you can figure out how to detect edges in a picture. Then, you might say, if there are many straight edges, then it&rsquo;s a table.</p>\r\n<p id=\"e9bf\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">However, this kind of approach gets tricky pretty quickly. What if there&rsquo;s a white dog in the picture with no brown hair? What if the picture shows only the round parts of the table?</p>\r\n<p id=\"db40\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\"><span class=\"markup--strong markup--p-strong\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">This is where machine learning comes in.</span></p>\r\n<p id=\"316d\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\"><span class=\"markup--quote markup--p-quote is-other\" style=\"transition: background-color 0.2s ease 0s; cursor: pointer; background-color: transparent !important; background-image: linear-gradient(#defad3, #defad3);\" data-creator-ids=\"anon\">Machine learning typically implements an algorithm that automatically detects a pattern in the given input.</span></p>\r\n<p id=\"84d6\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">You can give, say, 1,000 pictures of a dog and 1,000 pictures of a table to a machine learning algorithm. Then, it will learn the difference between a dog and a table. When you give it a new picture of either a dog or a table, it will be able to recognize which one it is.</p>\r\n<p id=\"cd75\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">I think this is somewhat similar to how a baby learns new things. How does a baby learn that one thing looks like a dog and another a table? Probably from a bunch of examples.</p>\r\n<p id=\"25db\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">You probably don&rsquo;t explicitly tell a baby, &ldquo;If something is furry and has light brown hair, then it&rsquo;s probably a dog.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p id=\"d111\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">You would probably just say, &ldquo;That&rsquo;s a dog. This is also a dog. And this one is a table. That one is also a table.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p id=\"20cf\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">Machine learning algorithms work much the same way.</p>\r\n<p id=\"5c9c\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">You can apply the same idea to:</p>\r\n<ul class=\"postList\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none none; counter-reset: post 0; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84); font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, \'Open Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', sans-serif; font-size: 20px;\">\r\n<li id=\"6385\" class=\"graf graf--li graf-after--p\" style=\"margin-left: 30px; margin-bottom: 14px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em;\">recommendation systems (think YouTube, Amazon, and Netflix)</li>\r\n<li id=\"9f92\" class=\"graf graf--li graf-after--li\" style=\"margin-left: 30px; margin-bottom: 14px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em;\">face recognition</li>\r\n<li id=\"c048\" class=\"graf graf--li graf-after--li\" style=\"margin-left: 30px; margin-bottom: 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em;\">voice recognition</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p id=\"d380\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--li\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">among other applications.</p>\r\n<p id=\"1e17\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">Popular machine learning algorithms you might have heard about include:</p>\r\n<ul class=\"postList\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none none; counter-reset: post 0; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84); font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, \'Open Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', sans-serif; font-size: 20px;\">\r\n<li id=\"c04d\" class=\"graf graf--li graf-after--p\" style=\"margin-left: 30px; margin-bottom: 14px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em;\">Neural networks</li>\r\n<li id=\"526d\" class=\"graf graf--li graf-after--li\" style=\"margin-left: 30px; margin-bottom: 14px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em;\">Deep learning</li>\r\n<li id=\"84cb\" class=\"graf graf--li graf-after--li\" style=\"margin-left: 30px; margin-bottom: 14px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em;\">Support vector machines</li>\r\n<li id=\"04b1\" class=\"graf graf--li graf-after--li\" style=\"margin-left: 30px; margin-bottom: 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em;\">Random forest</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p id=\"e5ae\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--li\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">You can use any of the above algorithms to solve the picture-labeling problem I explained earlier.</p>\r\n<h4 id=\"2f9b\" class=\"graf graf--h4 graf-after--p\" style=\"font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, \'Lucida Grande\', \'Lucida Sans Unicode\', \'Lucida Sans\', Geneva, Arial, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -0.012em; margin: 30px 0px 0px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84); --baseline-multiplier: 0.22; font-size: 26px; line-height: 1.22;\"><span class=\"markup--strong markup--h4-strong\" style=\"font-weight: inherit;\">Python for machine&nbsp;learning</span></h4>\r\n<p id=\"b063\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--h4\" style=\"margin: 6px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">There are popular machine learning libraries and frameworks for Python.</p>\r\n<p id=\"5d93\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">Two of the most popular ones are&nbsp;<span class=\"markup--strong markup--p-strong\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">scikit-learn</span>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<span class=\"markup--strong markup--p-strong\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">TensorFlow</span>.</p>\r\n<ul class=\"postList\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none none; counter-reset: post 0; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84); font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, \'Open Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', sans-serif; font-size: 20px;\">\r\n<li id=\"e498\" class=\"graf graf--li graf-after--p\" style=\"margin-left: 30px; margin-bottom: 14px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em;\">scikit-learn comes with some of the more popular machine learning algorithms built-in. I mentioned some of them above.</li>\r\n<li id=\"4f58\" class=\"graf graf--li graf-after--li\" style=\"margin-left: 30px; margin-bottom: 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em;\">TensorFlow is more of a low-level library that allows you to build custom machine learning algorithms.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p id=\"6281\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--li\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">If you&rsquo;re just getting started with a machine learning project, I would recommend that you first start with scikit-learn. If you start running into efficiency issues, then I would start looking into TensorFlow.</p>\r\n<h4 id=\"f3cc\" class=\"graf graf--h4 graf-after--p\" style=\"font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, \'Lucida Grande\', \'Lucida Sans Unicode\', \'Lucida Sans\', Geneva, Arial, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -0.012em; margin: 30px 0px 0px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84); --baseline-multiplier: 0.22; font-size: 26px; line-height: 1.22;\"><span class=\"markup--strong markup--h4-strong\" style=\"font-weight: inherit;\">How should I learn machine learning?</span></h4>\r\n<p id=\"6379\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--h4\" style=\"margin: 6px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">To learn machine learning fundamentals, I would recommend either&nbsp;<a class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" style=\"background-color: transparent; text-decoration-line: none; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54); background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: linear-gradient(to right, currentcolor 100%, currentcolor 0px); background-size: 1px 1px; background-position: 0px calc(1em + 1px);\" href=\"https://www.coursera.org/learn/machine-learning\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-href=\"https://www.coursera.org/learn/machine-learning\">Stanford&rsquo;s</a>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<a class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" style=\"background-color: transparent; text-decoration-line: none; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54); background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: linear-gradient(to right, currentcolor 100%, currentcolor 0px); background-size: 1px 1px; background-position: 0px calc(1em + 1px);\" href=\"https://work.caltech.edu/telecourse.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-href=\"https://work.caltech.edu/telecourse.html\">Caltech&rsquo;s</a>&nbsp;machine learning course.</p>\r\n<p id=\"b5fe\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">Please note that you need basic knowledge of calculus and linear algebra to understand some of the materials in those courses.</p>\r\n<p id=\"9aa3\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">Then, I would practice what you&rsquo;ve learned from one of those courses with&nbsp;<a class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" style=\"background-color: transparent; text-decoration-line: none; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54); background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: linear-gradient(to right, currentcolor 100%, currentcolor 0px); background-size: 1px 1px; background-position: 0px calc(1em + 1px);\" href=\"https://www.kaggle.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-href=\"https://www.kaggle.com/\">Kaggle</a>. It&rsquo;s a website where people compete to build the best machine learning algorithm for a given problem. They have nice tutorials for beginners, too.</p>\r\n<h3 id=\"b464\" class=\"graf graf--h3 graf-after--p\" style=\"font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, \'Lucida Grande\', \'Lucida Sans Unicode\', \'Lucida Sans\', Geneva, Arial, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -0.015em; margin: 56px 0px 0px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84); --baseline-multiplier: 0.22; font-size: 34px; line-height: 1.15;\"><span class=\"markup--strong markup--h3-strong\">What about data analysis and data visualization?</span></h3>\r\n<p id=\"5a16\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--h3\" style=\"margin: 8px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">To help you understand what these might look like, let me give you a simple example here.</p>\r\n<p id=\"a832\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">Let&rsquo;s say you&rsquo;re working for a company that sells some products online.</p>\r\n<p id=\"492c\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">Then, as a data analyst, you might draw a bar graph like this.</p>\r\n<figure id=\"b12f\" class=\"graf graf--figure graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 43px 0px 0px; position: relative; clear: both; outline: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; user-select: auto; z-index: 100; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84); font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, \'Open Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', sans-serif; font-size: 20px;\">\r\n<div class=\"aspectRatioPlaceholder is-locked\" style=\"position: relative; width: 700px; margin: 0px auto; max-width: 700px; max-height: 467px;\">\r\n<div class=\"aspectRatioPlaceholder-fill\" style=\"padding-bottom: 466.891px;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"progressiveMedia js-progressiveMedia graf-image is-canvasLoaded is-imageLoaded\" style=\"position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 700px; height: 466.891px; margin: auto; box-sizing: border-box; background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); transition: background 0.2s ease 0s; cursor: zoom-in; max-width: 100%;\" data-image-id=\"1*62T-rtheKPehgZdPTEpKww.png\" data-width=\"3000\" data-height=\"2000\" data-action=\"zoom\" data-action-value=\"1*62T-rtheKPehgZdPTEpKww.png\" data-scroll=\"native\"><canvas class=\"progressiveMedia-canvas js-progressiveMedia-canvas\" style=\"display: block; vertical-align: baseline; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 700px; height: 466.891px; margin: auto; box-sizing: border-box; visibility: hidden; opacity: 0; backface-visibility: hidden; transition: visibility 0s linear 0.5s, opacity 0.1s ease 0.4s;\" width=\"75\" height=\"50\"></canvas><img class=\"progressiveMedia-image js-progressiveMedia-image\" style=\"border: 0px; display: block; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 700px; height: 466.891px; margin: auto; box-sizing: border-box; z-index: 100; visibility: visible; opacity: 1; backface-visibility: hidden; transition: visibility 0s linear 0s, opacity 0.4s ease 0s;\" src=\"https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/1600/1*62T-rtheKPehgZdPTEpKww.png\" alt=\"\" data-src=\"https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/1600/1*62T-rtheKPehgZdPTEpKww.png\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<figcaption class=\"imageCaption\" style=\"position: relative; left: 0px; width: 700px; top: 0px; margin-top: 10px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.68); outline: 0px; text-align: center; z-index: 300; --baseline-multiplier: 0.22; font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, \'Lucida Grande\', \'Lucida Sans Unicode\', \'Lucida Sans\', Geneva, Arial, sans-serif; font-feature-settings: \'liga\', \'lnum\'; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4; letter-spacing: 0px;\">Bar Chart 1 &mdash; generated with&nbsp;Python</figcaption></figure>\r\n<p id=\"9196\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--figure\" style=\"margin: 38px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">From this graph, we can tell that men bought over 400 units of this product and women bought about 350 units of this product this particular Sunday.</p>\r\n<p id=\"81fa\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">As a data analyst, you might come up with a few possible explanations for this difference.</p>\r\n<p id=\"7b19\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">One obvious possible explanation is that this product is more popular with men than with women. Another possible explanation might be that the sample size is too small and this difference was caused just by chance. And yet another possible explanation might be that men tend to buy this product more only on Sunday for some reason.</p>\r\n<p id=\"18ae\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">To understand which of these explanations is correct, you might draw another graph like this one.</p>\r\n<figure id=\"f610\" class=\"graf graf--figure graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 43px 0px 0px; position: relative; clear: both; outline: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; user-select: auto; z-index: 100; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84); font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, \'Open Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', sans-serif; font-size: 20px;\">\r\n<div class=\"aspectRatioPlaceholder is-locked\" style=\"position: relative; width: 700px; margin: 0px auto; max-width: 700px; max-height: 467px;\">\r\n<div class=\"aspectRatioPlaceholder-fill\" style=\"padding-bottom: 466.891px;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"progressiveMedia js-progressiveMedia graf-image is-canvasLoaded is-imageLoaded\" style=\"position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 700px; height: 466.891px; margin: auto; box-sizing: border-box; background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); transition: background 0.2s ease 0s; cursor: zoom-in; max-width: 100%;\" data-image-id=\"1*VgNfqK5XxNfHxx6S4VFCjQ.png\" data-width=\"3000\" data-height=\"2000\" data-action=\"zoom\" data-action-value=\"1*VgNfqK5XxNfHxx6S4VFCjQ.png\" data-scroll=\"native\"><canvas class=\"progressiveMedia-canvas js-progressiveMedia-canvas\" style=\"display: block; vertical-align: baseline; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 700px; height: 466.891px; margin: auto; box-sizing: border-box; visibility: hidden; opacity: 0; backface-visibility: hidden; transition: visibility 0s linear 0.5s, opacity 0.1s ease 0.4s;\" width=\"75\" height=\"50\"></canvas><img class=\"progressiveMedia-image js-progressiveMedia-image\" style=\"border: 0px; display: block; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 700px; height: 466.891px; margin: auto; box-sizing: border-box; z-index: 100; visibility: visible; opacity: 1; backface-visibility: hidden; transition: visibility 0s linear 0s, opacity 0.4s ease 0s;\" src=\"https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/1600/1*VgNfqK5XxNfHxx6S4VFCjQ.png\" alt=\"\" data-src=\"https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/1600/1*VgNfqK5XxNfHxx6S4VFCjQ.png\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<figcaption class=\"imageCaption\" style=\"position: relative; left: 0px; width: 700px; top: 0px; margin-top: 10px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.68); outline: 0px; text-align: center; z-index: 300; --baseline-multiplier: 0.22; font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, \'Lucida Grande\', \'Lucida Sans Unicode\', \'Lucida Sans\', Geneva, Arial, sans-serif; font-feature-settings: \'liga\', \'lnum\'; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4; letter-spacing: 0px;\">Line Chart 1 &mdash; generated with&nbsp;Python</figcaption></figure>\r\n<p id=\"e005\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--figure\" style=\"margin: 38px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">Instead of showing the data for Sunday only, we&rsquo;re looking at the data for a full week. As you can see, from this graph, we can see that this difference is pretty consistent over different days.</p>\r\n<p id=\"659c\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">From this little analysis, you might conclude that the most convincing explanation for this difference is that this product is simply more popular with men than with women.</p>\r\n<p id=\"29b9\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">On the other hand, what if you see a graph like this one instead?</p>\r\n<figure id=\"04cf\" class=\"graf graf--figure graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 43px 0px 0px; position: relative; clear: both; outline: 0px; box-sizing: border-box; user-select: auto; z-index: 100; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84); font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, \'Open Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', sans-serif; font-size: 20px;\">\r\n<div class=\"aspectRatioPlaceholder is-locked\" style=\"position: relative; width: 700px; margin: 0px auto; max-width: 700px; max-height: 467px;\">\r\n<div class=\"aspectRatioPlaceholder-fill\" style=\"padding-bottom: 466.891px;\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div class=\"progressiveMedia js-progressiveMedia graf-image is-canvasLoaded is-imageLoaded\" style=\"position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 700px; height: 466.891px; margin: auto; box-sizing: border-box; background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0); transition: background 0.2s ease 0s; cursor: zoom-in; max-width: 100%;\" data-image-id=\"1*dMpu_fd-THNXRJhHIq2O3g.png\" data-width=\"3000\" data-height=\"2000\" data-action=\"zoom\" data-action-value=\"1*dMpu_fd-THNXRJhHIq2O3g.png\" data-scroll=\"native\"><canvas class=\"progressiveMedia-canvas js-progressiveMedia-canvas\" style=\"display: block; vertical-align: baseline; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 700px; height: 466.891px; margin: auto; box-sizing: border-box; visibility: hidden; opacity: 0; backface-visibility: hidden; transition: visibility 0s linear 0.5s, opacity 0.1s ease 0.4s;\" width=\"75\" height=\"50\"></canvas><img class=\"progressiveMedia-image js-progressiveMedia-image\" style=\"border: 0px; display: block; position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px; width: 700px; height: 466.891px; margin: auto; box-sizing: border-box; z-index: 100; visibility: visible; opacity: 1; backface-visibility: hidden; transition: visibility 0s linear 0s, opacity 0.4s ease 0s;\" src=\"https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/1600/1*dMpu_fd-THNXRJhHIq2O3g.png\" alt=\"\" data-src=\"https://cdn-images-1.medium.com/max/1600/1*dMpu_fd-THNXRJhHIq2O3g.png\" /></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<figcaption class=\"imageCaption\" style=\"position: relative; left: 0px; width: 700px; top: 0px; margin-top: 10px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.68); outline: 0px; text-align: center; z-index: 300; --baseline-multiplier: 0.22; font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, \'Lucida Grande\', \'Lucida Sans Unicode\', \'Lucida Sans\', Geneva, Arial, sans-serif; font-feature-settings: \'liga\', \'lnum\'; font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4; letter-spacing: 0px;\">Line Chart 2 &mdash; also generated with&nbsp;Python</figcaption></figure>\r\n<p id=\"7487\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--figure\" style=\"margin: 38px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">Then, what explains the difference on Sunday?</p>\r\n<p id=\"bfa8\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">You might say, perhaps men tend to buy more of this product only on Sunday for some reason. Or, perhaps it was just a coincidence that men bought more of it on Sunday.</p>\r\n<p id=\"e663\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">So, this is a simplified example of what data analysis might look like in the real world.</p>\r\n<p id=\"863f\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">The data analysis work I did when I was working at Google and Microsoft was very similar to this example &mdash; only more complex. I actually used Python at Google for this kind of analysis, while I used JavaScript at Microsoft.</p>\r\n<p id=\"0bc2\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">I used SQL at both of those companies to pull data from our databases. Then, I would use either Python and Matplotlib (at Google) or JavaScript and D3.js (at Microsoft) to visualize and analyze this data.</p>\r\n<h4 id=\"bfa9\" class=\"graf graf--h4 graf-after--p\" style=\"font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, \'Lucida Grande\', \'Lucida Sans Unicode\', \'Lucida Sans\', Geneva, Arial, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -0.012em; margin: 30px 0px 0px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84); --baseline-multiplier: 0.22; font-size: 26px; line-height: 1.22;\"><span class=\"markup--strong markup--h4-strong\" style=\"font-weight: inherit;\">Data analysis / visualization with&nbsp;Python</span></h4>\r\n<p id=\"ac33\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--h4\" style=\"margin: 6px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">One of the most popular libraries for data visualization is&nbsp;<a class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" style=\"background-color: transparent; text-decoration-line: none; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54); background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: linear-gradient(to right, currentcolor 100%, currentcolor 0px); background-size: 1px 1px; background-position: 0px calc(1em + 1px);\" href=\"https://matplotlib.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-href=\"https://matplotlib.org/\">Matplotlib</a>.</p>\r\n<p id=\"a766\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">It&rsquo;s a good library to get started with because:</p>\r\n<ul class=\"postList\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none none; counter-reset: post 0; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84); font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, \'Open Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', sans-serif; font-size: 20px;\">\r\n<li id=\"9659\" class=\"graf graf--li graf-after--p\" style=\"margin-left: 30px; margin-bottom: 14px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em;\">It&rsquo;s easy to get started with</li>\r\n<li id=\"6b61\" class=\"graf graf--li graf-after--li\" style=\"margin-left: 30px; margin-bottom: 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em;\">Some other libraries such as&nbsp;<a class=\"markup--anchor markup--li-anchor\" style=\"background-color: transparent; text-decoration-line: none; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54); background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: linear-gradient(to right, currentcolor 100%, currentcolor 0px); background-size: 1px 1px; background-position: 0px calc(1em + 1px);\" href=\"https://seaborn.pydata.org/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-href=\"https://seaborn.pydata.org/\">seaborn</a>&nbsp;is based on it. So, learning Matplotlib will help you learn these other libraries later on.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p id=\"9793\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--li\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\"><span class=\"markup--strong markup--p-strong\" style=\"font-weight: bold;\">How should I learn data analysis / visualization with Python?</span></p>\r\n<p id=\"04cb\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">You should first learn the fundamentals of data analysis and visualization. When I looked for good resources for this online, I couldn&rsquo;t find any. After learning the fundamentals of data analysis and visualization, learning fundamentals of statistics from websites like Coursera and Khan Academy will be helpful, as well.</p>\r\n<h3 id=\"f33f\" class=\"graf graf--h3 graf-after--p\" style=\"font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, \'Lucida Grande\', \'Lucida Sans Unicode\', \'Lucida Sans\', Geneva, Arial, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -0.015em; margin: 56px 0px 0px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84); --baseline-multiplier: 0.22; font-size: 34px; line-height: 1.15;\"><span class=\"markup--strong markup--h3-strong\">Scripting</span></h3>\r\n<h4 id=\"7756\" class=\"graf graf--h4 graf-after--h3\" style=\"font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, \'Lucida Grande\', \'Lucida Sans Unicode\', \'Lucida Sans\', Geneva, Arial, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -0.012em; margin: 31px 0px 0px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84); --baseline-multiplier: 0.22; font-size: 26px; line-height: 1.22;\"><span class=\"markup--strong markup--h4-strong\" style=\"font-weight: inherit;\">What is scripting?</span></h4>\r\n<p id=\"0eea\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--h4\" style=\"margin: 6px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">Scripting usually refers to writing small programs that are designed to automate simple tasks.</p>\r\n<p id=\"508e\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">So, let me give you an example from my personal experience here.</p>\r\n<p id=\"a503\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">I used to work at a small startup in Japan where we had an email support system. It was a system for us to respond to questions customers sent us via email.</p>\r\n<p id=\"0798\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">When I was working there, I had the task of counting the numbers of emails containing certain keywords so we could analyze the emails we received.</p>\r\n<p id=\"8f47\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">We could have done it manually, but instead, I wrote a simple program / simple script to automate this task.</p>\r\n<p id=\"ddd8\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">Actually, we used Ruby for this back then, but Python is also a good language for this kind of task. Python is suited for this type of task mainly because it has relatively simple syntax and is easy to write. It&rsquo;s also quick to write something small with it and test it.</p>\r\n<h3 id=\"8a44\" class=\"graf graf--h3 graf-after--p\" style=\"font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, \'Lucida Grande\', \'Lucida Sans Unicode\', \'Lucida Sans\', Geneva, Arial, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -0.015em; margin: 56px 0px 0px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84); --baseline-multiplier: 0.22; font-size: 34px; line-height: 1.15;\"><span class=\"markup--strong markup--h3-strong\">What about embedded applications?</span></h3>\r\n<p id=\"02b1\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--h3\" style=\"margin: 8px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">I&rsquo;m not an expert on embedded applications, but I know that Python works with Rasberry Pi. It seems like a popular application among hardware hobbyists.</p>\r\n<h3 id=\"b965\" class=\"graf graf--h3 graf-after--p\" style=\"font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, \'Lucida Grande\', \'Lucida Sans Unicode\', \'Lucida Sans\', Geneva, Arial, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -0.015em; margin: 56px 0px 0px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84); --baseline-multiplier: 0.22; font-size: 34px; line-height: 1.15;\"><span class=\"markup--strong markup--h3-strong\">What about&nbsp;gaming?</span></h3>\r\n<p id=\"737d\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--h3\" style=\"margin: 8px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">You could use the library called PyGame to develop games, but it&rsquo;s not the most popular gaming engine out there. You could use it to build a hobby project, but I personally wouldn&rsquo;t choose it if you&rsquo;re serious about game development.</p>\r\n<p id=\"ef14\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">Rather, I would recommend getting started with Unity with C#, which is one of the most popular gaming engines. It allows you to build a game for many platforms, including Mac, Windows, iOS, and Android.</p>\r\n<h3 id=\"fb74\" class=\"graf graf--h3 graf-after--p\" style=\"font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, \'Lucida Grande\', \'Lucida Sans Unicode\', \'Lucida Sans\', Geneva, Arial, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -0.015em; margin: 56px 0px 0px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84); --baseline-multiplier: 0.22; font-size: 34px; line-height: 1.15;\"><span class=\"markup--strong markup--h3-strong\">What about desktop applications?</span></h3>\r\n<p id=\"72cc\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--h3\" style=\"margin: 8px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">You could make one with Python using Tkinter, but it doesn&rsquo;t seem like the most popular choice either.</p>\r\n<p id=\"b068\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">Instead, it seems like languages like&nbsp;<a class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" style=\"background-color: transparent; text-decoration-line: none; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54); background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: linear-gradient(to right, currentcolor 100%, currentcolor 0px); background-size: 1px 1px; background-position: 0px calc(1em + 1px);\" href=\"https://www.quora.com/What-is-the-best-programming-language-to-develop-a-desktop-application-It-should-be-cross-platform-free-easy-to-learn-and-have-a-good-community\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-href=\"https://www.quora.com/What-is-the-best-programming-language-to-develop-a-desktop-application-It-should-be-cross-platform-free-easy-to-learn-and-have-a-good-community\">Java, C#, and C++</a>&nbsp;are more popular for this.</p>\r\n<p id=\"7409\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">Recently, some companies have started using JavaScript to create Desktop applications, too.</p>\r\n<p id=\"029f\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\"><a class=\"markup--anchor markup--p-anchor\" style=\"background-color: transparent; text-decoration-line: none; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.54); background-repeat: repeat-x; background-image: linear-gradient(to right, currentcolor 100%, currentcolor 0px); background-size: 1px 1px; background-position: 0px calc(1em + 1px);\" href=\"https://slack.engineering/building-hybrid-applications-with-electron-dc67686de5fb\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" data-href=\"https://slack.engineering/building-hybrid-applications-with-electron-dc67686de5fb\">For example, Slack&rsquo;s desktop app was built with something called Electron</a>. It allows you to build desktop applications with JavaScript.</p>\r\n<p id=\"f362\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">Personally, if I was building a desktop application, I would go with a JavaScript option. It allows you to reuse some of the code from a web version if you have it.</p>\r\n<p id=\"2298\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">However, I&rsquo;m not an expert on desktop applications either, so please let me know in a comment if you disagree or agree with me on this.</p>\r\n<h3 id=\"2243\" class=\"graf graf--h3 graf-after--p\" style=\"font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, \'Lucida Grande\', \'Lucida Sans Unicode\', \'Lucida Sans\', Geneva, Arial, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -0.015em; margin: 56px 0px 0px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84); --baseline-multiplier: 0.22; font-size: 34px; line-height: 1.15;\"><span class=\"markup--strong markup--h3-strong\">Python 3 or Python&nbsp;2?</span></h3>\r\n<p id=\"2a2b\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--h3\" style=\"margin: 8px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">I would recommend Python 3 since it&rsquo;s more modern and it&rsquo;s a more popular option at this point.</p>\r\n<h3 id=\"db9f\" class=\"graf graf--h3 graf-after--p\" style=\"font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, \'Lucida Grande\', \'Lucida Sans Unicode\', \'Lucida Sans\', Geneva, Arial, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -0.015em; margin: 56px 0px 0px; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84); --baseline-multiplier: 0.22; font-size: 34px; line-height: 1.15;\"><span class=\"markup--strong markup--h3-strong\">Footnote: A note about back-end code vs front-end code (just in case you are not familiar with the&nbsp;terms):</span></h3>\r\n<p id=\"3280\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--h3\" style=\"margin: 8px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">Let&rsquo;s say you want to make something like Instagram.</p>\r\n<p id=\"87f9\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">Then, you&rsquo;d need to create front-end code for each type of device you want to support.</p>\r\n<p id=\"12dc\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">You might use, for example:</p>\r\n<ul class=\"postList\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none none; counter-reset: post 0; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84); font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, \'Open Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', sans-serif; font-size: 20px;\">\r\n<li id=\"8a74\" class=\"graf graf--li graf-after--p\" style=\"margin-left: 30px; margin-bottom: 14px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em;\">Swift for iOS</li>\r\n<li id=\"a322\" class=\"graf graf--li graf-after--li\" style=\"margin-left: 30px; margin-bottom: 14px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em;\">Java for Android</li>\r\n<li id=\"db28\" class=\"graf graf--li graf-after--li\" style=\"margin-left: 30px; margin-bottom: 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em;\">JavaScript for web browsers</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p id=\"d0fa\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--li\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">Each set of code will run on each type of device / browser. This will be the set of code that determines what the layout of the app will be like, what the buttons should look like when you click them, etc.</p>\r\n<p id=\"270d\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">However, you will still need the ability to store users&rsquo; info and photos. You will want to store them on your server and not just on your users&rsquo; devices so each user&rsquo;s followers can view his/her photos.</p>\r\n<p id=\"4ff3\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">This is where the backend code / server-side code comes in. You&rsquo;ll need to write some backend code to do things like:</p>\r\n<ul class=\"postList\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; padding: 0px; list-style: none none; counter-reset: post 0; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84); font-family: medium-content-sans-serif-font, -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, \'Segoe UI\', Roboto, Oxygen, Ubuntu, Cantarell, \'Open Sans\', \'Helvetica Neue\', sans-serif; font-size: 20px;\">\r\n<li id=\"95e8\" class=\"graf graf--li graf-after--p\" style=\"margin-left: 30px; margin-bottom: 14px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em;\">Keep track of who&rsquo;s following who</li>\r\n<li id=\"446e\" class=\"graf graf--li graf-after--li\" style=\"margin-left: 30px; margin-bottom: 14px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em;\">Compress photos so they don&rsquo;t take up so much storage space</li>\r\n<li id=\"9fda\" class=\"graf graf--li graf-after--li\" style=\"margin-left: 30px; margin-bottom: 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em;\">Recommend photos and new accounts to each user in the<em class=\"markup--em markup--li-em\" style=\"font-feature-settings: \'liga\', \'salt\';\">&nbsp;discovery</em>&nbsp;feature</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p id=\"58c7\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--li\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">So, this is the difference between backend code and front-end code.</p>\r\n<p id=\"fd54\" class=\"graf graf--p graf-after--p\" style=\"margin: 29px 0px 0px; --baseline-multiplier: 0.17; font-family: medium-content-serif-font, Georgia, Cambria, \'Times New Roman\', Times, serif; font-size: 21px; line-height: 1.58; letter-spacing: -0.003em; color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.84);\">By the way, Python is not the only good choice for writing backend / server-side code. There are many other popular choices, including Node.js, which is based on JavaScript.</p>','2018-12-14 00:36:39','2018-12-14 00:39:41'),(4,4,1,'5 Things You Didn’t Know About Java','<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; margin: 0px 0px 20px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: #111111;\">So, you&rsquo;ve been working with Java since the very beginning? Remember the days when it was called &ldquo;Oak&rdquo;, when OO was still a hot topic, when C++ folks thought that Java had no chance, when Applets were still a thing?</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; margin: 0px 0px 20px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: #111111;\">I bet that you didn&rsquo;t know at least half of the following things. Let&rsquo;s start this week with some great surprises about the inner workings of Java.</p>\r\n<h2 style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 5.8rem; font-weight: 400; margin: 0px 0px 20px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; clear: both; line-height: 0.96552; color: #111111;\">1. There is no such thing as a checked exception</h2>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; margin: 0px 0px 20px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: #111111;\">That&rsquo;s right! The JVM doesn&rsquo;t know any such thing, only the Java language does.</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; margin: 0px 0px 20px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: #111111;\">Today, everyone agrees that checked exceptions were a mistake. As&nbsp;<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-family: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: #2390bb; text-decoration-line: none; transition: all 0.2s ease 0s;\" href=\"http://www.geecon.cz/speakers/?id=2\">Bruce Eckel said on his closing keynote at GeeCON, Prague</a>, no other language after Java has engaged in using checked exceptions, and even Java 8 does no longer embrace them in the new Streams API (<a style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-family: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: #2390bb; text-decoration-line: none; transition: all 0.2s ease 0s;\" title=\"Java 8 Friday: Better Exceptions\" href=\"https://blog.jooq.org/2014/05/23/java-8-friday-better-exceptions/\">which can actually be a bit of a pain, when your lambdas use IO or JDBC</a>).</p>\r\n<p style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; margin: 0px 0px 20px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: #111111;\">Do you want proof that the JVM doesn&rsquo;t know such a thing? Try the following code:</p>\r\n<div style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-family: \'Open Sans\', sans-serif; font-size: 16px; margin: 0px; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; color: #111111;\">\r\n<div id=\"highlighter_514517\" class=\"syntaxhighlighter  java\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; border: 0px; font-family: inherit; font-weight: inherit; font-style: inherit; outline: 0px; padding: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; width: 661.5px; font-size: 1em !important; margin: 1em 0px !important; position: relative !important; overflow: auto hidden !important;\">\r\n<table style=\"width: 661px; box-sizing: content-box !important; border: 0px !important; font-family: Monaco, Consolas, \'Bitstream Vera Sans Mono\', \'Courier New\', Courier, monospace !important; font-size: 1em !important; margin: 0px !important; outline: 0px !important; padding: 0px !important; vertical-align: baseline !important; border-radius: 0px !important; background: none !important; bottom: auto !important; float: none !important; height: auto !important; left: auto !important; line-height: 1.1em !important; overflow: visible !important; position: static !important; right: auto !important; top: auto !important; direction: ltr !important; box-shadow: none !important; table-layout: auto !important;\" border=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody style=\"box-sizing: content-box !important; border: 0px !important; font-size: 1em !important; margin: 0px !important; outline: 0px !important; padding: 0px !important; vertical-align: baseline !important; border-radius: 0px !important; background: none !important; bottom: auto !important; float: none !important; height: auto !important; left: auto !important; line-height: 1.1em !important; overflow: visible !important; position: stat